Title: Spring Boot REST API - Vendor Management

This is my first backend REST API project built with Spring Boot.
It performs basic CRUD operations on a Vendor entity and is tested using Postman.

1.) Features
- Create a new vendor
- Retrieve all vendors
- Update vendor details
- Delete a vendor

2.) Technologies Used
- Java 17
- Spring Boot
- Postman
- IntelliJ IDEA

3.) How to Run
1. Clone the repository
2. Open in IntelliJ IDEA
3. Run `CloudVendorApplication.java`
4. Use Postman to hit endpoints

4.) Sample POST Request
POST /vendors
Content-Type: application/json
{
"vendorId": "101",
"vendorName": "AWS",
"vendorAddress": "USA",
"vendorPhoneNumber": "1234567890"
}

5.) Status
Completed and tested with Postman.

